page.title: 20THE KEMPSEY SURVEYORS.
page.content: The survey of the Kempsey and Norton area was carried out in the Summer of 1985 by children and staff of Nunnery Wood High School in Worcester. The surveyors themselves would like to thank all the people in the Kempsey and Norton area for their enormous help and in particular Gillian Barnett and Catherine Oram of Kempsey Primary School who told us about their school for the survey. The pupils from Nunnery Wood were all in there second year (ages 12 to 13) and were Emma Scoular, Richard Beale, Leon Burton, and Jason Moseley. Their teacher was Mr.Michael Leydon. The survey itself was carried out in the Summer when the World's Pop Stars came together in an attempt to raise large amounts of money to help feed the starving people in Ethiopia.
